d over, the mob is tougher and you kill less per a hour but it still becomes routine.<br>
<br>
That is why I wish fights were different, I wish Verant would alter things and mix it up. Such fights as the 10th ring, ring of fire, burrower parasite, grimling war, ring of vulak, Shei, and maybe afew others are really quite cool because they are different and dont follow the so common routine of most uber encounters. People actually have to think a little more in these fights and be on their toes. I love a fight where right from the getgo you are constantly having to think and alter your current action as the scene changes around you. If you have ever fought the final mob in the ring of slime you will know the kind of fight that makes me sick of the same ole same ole. Dain, Yelinak, AoW, KTMax, Statue, Rhags 1 and 2, THO, IV, Grieg, Tunare, CT, and many more fights are all borring and sin and almost indistinguishable from one another. Sure there are slight differences but they are window dressing, they are still MT + CH chain fights of atrition. A fight like AoW might be tough but only because he dishes such a sick amount of damage in one flurry round that a tank nearly dies often, if a cleric misses his mark the tank dies and all is lost. But that fight still is simple in theory and takes pure timeing of heals to make it easy, no thinking is involved beyond making sure you time your heal right. No thinking is involved for a melee except to stay at max melee range and unengage at tank changes either so dont think I am saying only clerics have it easy, we all do. This game is not a game of strategy for most fights, it is a game of clicking talent and following pre-made fighting strategy. I want to have to think and adapt in battles to changing situations.<br>
<br>
This really reminds me of a post I just read, a person stated they had bought a cheat book on pac-man. Supposedly all you have to do is follow the path laid out in the book and you will alwasys avoid the ghosts since they are programed to move the exact same way every time. Well that's EQ in a nutshell. If you follow the preordained path every time for each fight exactly the same then you are guarenteed success. And so many of the various mobs have very similar paths it just gets old. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/upigboyph.showPublicProfile?language=EN>PigboyPH</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>I Live Here</span><br>  Posts: 1296<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(8/9/02 11:40:31 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3124.topic&index=50>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Diversity n classes</span><hr size=1> Maybe this is the wrong game for you?<br>
